{PLACE OF WORK SURVEY(CONT) }
CONCLUSIONS:
a) Gilberdyke is a rural village, many adults work on the land or in jobs associated with farming. b) Many parents are employed in the village in the service industries eg. at the health centre, as shop asssistants or barmaids c) A large majority of workers who travel outside the village go towards Hull. So, although nearer Goole/Howden in actual distance, Gilberdyke has stronger ties with the Hull area. d) A surprisingly high number of parents work outside the area, travelling long distances to work, although this group does include split family details.
